  "body": "I was connected to the ETH1 node via an SSH tunnel.  The SSH connection droped and I had to recreate it.  Teku restored the connection to the eth1 node but didn’t recreate the filter it was using to track head blocks:\n\n```\n2020-05-09 22:48:48.841+00:00 | pool-11-thread-3 | ERROR | Filter | Error sending request\norg.web3j.protocol.exceptions.ClientConnectionException: Invalid response received: 400; {\n  \"jsonrpc\" : \"2.0\",\n  \"id\" : 4797,\n  \"error\" : {\n    \"code\" : -32000,\n    \"message\" : \"Filter not found\"\n  }\n}\n        at org.web3j.protocol.http.HttpService.performIO(HttpService.java:173) ~[core-4.5.6.jar:?]\n        at org.web3j.protocol.Service.send(Service.java:42) ~[core-4.5.6.jar:?]\n        at org.web3j.protocol.core.Request.send(Request.java:81) ~[core-4.5.6.jar:?]\n        at org.web3j.protocol.core.filters.Filter.pollFilter(Filter.java:128) ~[core-4.5.6.jar:?]\n        at org.web3j.protocol.core.filters.Filter.lambda$run$0(Filter.java:92) ~[core-4.5.6.jar:?]\n        at java.util.concurrent.Executors$RunnableAdapter.call(Executors.java:515) [?:?]\n        at java.util.concurrent.FutureTask.runAndReset(FutureTask.java:305) [?:?]\n        at java.util.concurrent.ScheduledThreadPoolExecutor$ScheduledFutureTask.run(ScheduledThreadPoolExecutor.java:305) [?:?]\n        at java.util.concurrent.ThreadPoolExecutor.runWorker(ThreadPoolExecutor.java:1128) [?:?]\n        at java.util.concurrent.ThreadPoolExecutor$Worker.run(ThreadPoolExecutor.java:628) [?:?]\n        at java.lang.Thread.run(Thread.java:834) [?:?]\n\n```\n",
